        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-11-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-11-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="270" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d270">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Marshall</persName> to President
                            <persName type="to">Truman</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="12" xml:id="d270fn12">Copy transmitted to the Acting Secretary of State
                        by the War Department on November 11.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-11-11">November 11,
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1745. <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. President</hi>: Now at 10 p.m. Monday I have
                    just been informed by message from Generalissimo that at urgent request of
                    non-party delegation he has agreed to delay convocation of National Assembly 3
                    days. They promised that if such delay was granted the Third Party organizations
                    would submit names of their delegates and possibly the Communists but I think
                    the last unlikely.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>G. C. <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
